HEADWORD: Nome
<hw>Nome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to deal
out, distribute.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A province or political
division, as of modern Greece or ancient Egypt; a nomarchy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any melody determined by inviolable rules.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

